Ever shaved your legs or hands and noticed tiny dark dots after? That’s called *strawberry skin* – and no, it’s not cute like the fruit 🍓

It happens when pores or hair follicles get clogged or irritated after shaving. But don’t worry – you can avoid it! ✨

Here’s how to shave the *right* way to keep your skin smooth and bump-free:

👉 Always use a **fresh, clean razor** – blunt or rusted ones can irritate your skin and cause tiny bumps
👉 **Exfoliate** your skin gently before shaving – this removes dead skin and helps the razor glide better
👉 Always shave in the **direction of your hair growth** – less friction = less irritation
👉 Use a good **shaving gel or foam or like I have used conditioner– never dry shave!
👉 Rinse with **cold water** after shaving to close the pores
👉 Moisturise right after – keep that skin hydrated and happy 💦

Your skin deserves love – not red dots and rough patches. 💖 Try this next time and thank me later!
